		<div id="comment_body_64761208"><p>When I served in the Navy (not the US one) more than 30 years ago, the ship officers had a PC/XT clone with some special software that was assigned to them to perform tasks related to combat readiness, personnel training and so on. It was supposed to be kept secret. However, they regularly brought unapproved floppies with pirated games and abused the computer. The sh!t did hit the fan when they accidentally (?) brought a virus that deleted their special software and everything else, and I as a seaman with considerable computing skills had to cover up the incident to their superiors and recover the files with considerable effort.</p><p>Some things never change, I guess.</p></div>
