		<div id="comment_body_64761284">The networks they have are at max utilization at times with tactical data. Before Starlink, how would they even do it? Since this event, the Navy has been adding Starlink to ships. The process to add features to a ship is a long one, to make sure they don't interfere with critical systems. Even just power on a ship is carefully managed. The biggest hurdle is actually space. There is not a lot of extra space on smaller ships. Even a small starlink antenna can interfere with the operations of other equipment.</div>
	</div>

